---
import DocLayout from '../../layouts/DocLayout.astro';
import CodeBlock from '../../components/CodeBlock.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL || '/storyhouse-design-system/';
const currentPath = `${base}guides/migration`;
---

<DocLayout
  title="Migration Guide"
  description="Upgrade your project to the latest Storyhouse versions and migrate between major releases."
  currentPath={currentPath}
>
  <section>
    <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
    <p>
      This guide documents breaking changes, deprecations, and migration paths between Storyhouse
      versions. Always review the relevant section before upgrading.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 id="v0-1-to-v0-2">v0.1.0 (Alpha) to v0.2.0 (Beta)</h2>

    <div class="mb-6 inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-orange-100 px-3 py-1 text-sm font-medium text-orange-700 dark:bg-orange-950 dark:text-orange-300">
      Planned — no breaking changes released yet
    </div>

    <p>
      The current release (v0.1.0) is an alpha preview. The following changes are planned for the
      beta release and may require migration work:
    </p>

    <h3>Component Renames (Planned)</h3>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Current Name</th>
          <th>New Name</th>
          <th>Reason</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>Card</code></td>
          <td>Unchanged</td>
          <td>—</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>Button</code></td>
          <td>Unchanged</td>
          <td>—</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>Input</code></td>
          <td><code>TextField</code> <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-yellow-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium text-yellow-700 dark:bg-yellow-950 dark:text-yellow-300">Considered</span></td>
          <td>Align with form field naming conventions</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3>Package Restructuring (Planned)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><code>@storyhouse/components</code> will remain the main component package</li>
      <li><code>@storyhouse/tokens</code> will gain CSS variable output as the default export (currently requires explicit <code>/tokens.css</code> path)</li>
      <li><code>@storyhouse/utils</code> will export <code>cn()</code> as the default export</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Migration Steps (v0.1 → v0.2)</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <strong>Update imports</strong> if <code>Card</code> or <code>Input</code> are renamed.
        Use search-and-replace across your codebase:
        <CodeBlock lang="bash" title="Terminal" code={`# If Input becomes TextField
find src/ -type f -name '*.tsx' -exec sed -i 's/\\bInput\\b/TextField/g' {} +`} />
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Update token imports</strong> if path changes:
        <CodeBlock lang="diff" title="tokens-import.diff" code={`- import '@storyhouse/tokens/tokens.css';
+ import '@storyhouse/tokens';`} />
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Test all forms</strong> for any validation behavior changes
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 id="api-changes">API Compatibility Notes</h2>

    <h3>Button</h3>
    <p>
      The <code>Button</code> API is stable in v0.1.0. No prop changes are planned for the beta release.
      All current props (variant, size, isLoading, fullWidth, disabled) will continue working.
    </p>

    <h3>Card</h3>
    <p>
      The Card composable sub-component pattern (CardHeader, CardTitle, CardContent, CardFooter) is
      stable. The <code>variant</code> and <code>padding</code> props are final.
    </p>

    <h3>Input</h3>
    <p>
      The Input component may be renamed to <code>TextField</code> in v0.2.0 to better distinguish
      it from other form field types (Select, Textarea, etc.) that will be added in future releases.
      If this change happens, the old <code>Input</code> export will be deprecated with a warning
      for one minor version before removal.
    </p>

    <h3>Badge</h3>
    <p>
      Badge is stable. The Six-variant system (default, primary, success, warning, danger, neutral) is final.
      <code>dot</code> and <code>removable</code> props are stable.
    </p>

    <h3>Avatar</h3>
    <p>
      Avatar is stable. The five-size system (xs through xl) and two-shape system (circle, square) are final.
      The deterministic color algorithm is considered part of the public API — changing it would cause
      visual inconsistency across sessions.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 id="upgrade-checklist">Upgrade Checklist</h2>
    <p>When upgrading between any major versions, follow this checklist:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>Read the changelog for the target version</li>
      <li>Review the migration guide for breaking changes</li>
      <li>Update package.json version numbers</li>
      <li>Run <code>npm install</code> to update dependencies</li>
      <li>Run your test suite to catch regressions</li>
      <li>Run the build to verify no compilation errors</li>
      <li>Visually smoke-test all component pages in your app</li>
      <li>Check dark mode rendering for each component</li>
      <li>Verify Storybook renders correctly with the new version</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 id="legacy-code">Handling Legacy Code</h2>
    <p>
      If you're maintaining an older codebase and cannot immediately migrate, you can pin to a specific
      version in <code>package.json</code>:
    </p>

    <CodeBlock lang="json" title="package.json" code={`{
  "dependencies": {
    "@storyhouse/components": "0.1.x",
    "@storyhouse/tokens": "0.1.x"
  }
}`} />

    <p>
      The <code>0.1.x</code> range will receive patch updates (bug fixes) without breaking changes.
      Minor version bumps (0.2.0, 0.3.0) may include breaking changes until v1.0.0.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 id="v1-0-roadmap">v1.0.0 Roadmap</h2>
    <p>
      The v1.0.0 release will mark the stable, production-ready version of Storyhouse.
      Planned changes from alpha/v0.x:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>All component APIs are frozen (no breaking changes after v1.0)</li>
      <li>Tree-shakeable imports for smaller bundles</li>
      <li>Full CSS custom property coverage for all component colors</li>
      <li>Stable theme / dark mode API</li>
      <li>Semver compliance — breaking changes only in major versions</li>
      <li>Long-term support policy documentation</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</DocLayout>
